{"type":"message","id":"27b6423e","parentId":"c9ac9975","timestamp":"2026-03-29T15:42:52.533Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me analyze the results:\n\n1. **Git log for data/**: No output - means there's no git history for the data directory\n2. **ls -la data/**: Only 3 files - bills.json, habits.json, money.json\n3. **bills.json**: Has 4 bills - Electric Bill ($185), Internet ($79.99), Car Insurance ($145), and a \"Test Bill\" ($99.99)\n4. **money.json**: Only 2 paychecks recorded - March 1 and March 15, both $3,200\n5. **habits.json**: 3 habits with some completion dates\n\n\n6. **No backups found** - the find command only turned up the current bills.json file\n7. **Git HEAD**: Returned exit code 128, which typically means the file wasn't tracked in the previous commit\n\nThe data isn't actually gone - it's all there in the current files. The real issue seems to be that git history for the data directory is empty, the find command only located the active bills.json with no older versions or backups, and attempts to retrieve from the previous commit failed. The data appears to be intact, just without any version history to pull from.","thinkingSignature":"f9db41f595b2281e0e3b9d401feabcbfa55d10ac59378e78deef606a75b02638"},{"type":"text","text":"## Mission Control Data Recovery Check - Results\n\n### Git History\n- **`git log -- data/`**: No output — **no git history exists for the data directory**\n- **`git show HEAD:data/bills.json`**: Exit code 128 — **the data/ folder was never committed to git**\n\n### Current Files\nAll 3 data files exist and have content:\n\n**bills.json** (607 bytes):\n- Electric Bill - $185 (due 2026-04-05)\n- Internet - $79.99 (due 2026-04-10)\n- Car Insurance - $145 (due 2026-04-15)\n- Test Bill - $99.99 (due 2026-04-01)\n\n**money.json** (211 bytes):\n- Only 2 paychecks recorded: March 1 & March 15, $3,200 each\n\n**habits.json** (439 bytes):\n- Morning Workout (completed 3/27-3/29)\n- Read 20 mins (completed 3/27)\n- Drink 8 glasses water (completed 3/28)\n\n### Backup Search\n- No `.bak`, `.backup`, or old `bills*` files found anywhere\n\n### Verdict\n**The data is NOT lost** — all files exist with content. However:\n- The `data/` directory was **never tracked by git** (no history = no recovery possible via git)\n- There's **no backup system** in place\n\n**What appears to have happened**: The data exists but may have been reset recently (money.json only has 2 entries, missing other transactions). If something was deleted recently, it's gone — git never had it. The only way to recover would be from a Time Machine backup or other external backup system."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1291,"output":620,"cacheRead":15745,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":17656,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774798958043,"responseId":"06187b6e67ea2bbd70b585f282d63913"}}
